<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Opisthius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Opisthius</taxonomicName>
Kirby, 1837: 60. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Opisthius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="richardsoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Opisthius richardsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kirby, 1837 by monotypy. Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">opisthen</emphasis>
(behind) or 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">opisthios</emphasis>
(hinder) [masculine]. Bousquet and Smetana (1996: 218) suggested that the name possibly reflect 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kirby’s">Kirby's</normalizedToken>
assignment of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Opisthius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Opisthius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to follow 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Elaphrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Elaphrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in his paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="127" pageNumber="128">One North American species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
